# Vendored verbatim from
# https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/defeasable-logic/defeasable-logic.n3
# No truncation needed (51 lines upstream, reproduced unmodified below,
# including the upstream corpus's own spelling "defeasable" rather than the
# dictionary "defeasible"). Distinct mechanism vs. the already-vendored
# `snaf` case: `snaf` demonstrates a single `log:notIncludes` SNAF guard;
# this case chains TWO separate defeasible rules through the same closed-
# world-assumption mechanism (a defeater rule that marks penguins
# `:abnormal true`, then a default-flies rule guarded by
# `log:notIncludes { ?X :abnormal true }`, then a *second*, independent
# closed-world rule guarded by `log:notIncludes { ?X :flies true }`) --
# exercising interaction between two competing SNAF-guarded defaults over
# the same predicate, which `snaf` alone does not cover.
@prefix :     <http://example.org/defeasible#> .
@prefix log:  <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#> .
@prefix rdf:  <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xsd:  <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Strict facts
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
:tweety  a :Bird .
:polly   a :Penguin .

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Taxonomy: every penguin is a bird
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
{ ?X a :Penguin }  =>  { ?X a :Bird } .

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Defeater: penguins are abnormal with respect to flying
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
{ ?X a :Penguin }  =>  { ?X :abnormal true } .

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Defeasible default: birds (normally) fly
#  ----------------------------------------------------
#  The rule fires **only if** the current KB *does not* include
#  { ?X :abnormal true }  — that is SNAF via log:notIncludes.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
{
    ?X a :Bird .
    ?SCOPE log:notIncludes { ?X :abnormal true } .
}
=>
{
    ?X :flies true .
} .

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Closed-world *no-fly* conclusion
#  “If X is a bird and the current knowledge base does NOT already
#   contain { X :flies true } then assert { X :flies false }.”
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
{
    ?X     a :Bird .
    ?SCOPE log:notIncludes { ?X :flies true } .
}
=>
{ ?X :flies false } .

# query
{ ?X :flies ?Y } log:impliesAnswer { ?X :flies ?Y }.
